data.title: INTEGRIS Game Day Report: Thunder at Milwaukee Bucks – March 6, 2016
data.meta_description: MILWAUKEE – Breaking up the long four-game road trip with about 36 hours at home in Oklahoma City was the ideal way for the Thunder to prepare for one more road tilt before five days at home. As Head Coach Billy Donovan’s staff and players regrouped at the INTEGRIS Thunder Development Center on Saturday, they had a chance to work on itself as a group and scout its next opponent – the Milwaukee Bucks.
